raw_response:
Chocolate Peanut Butter Muffins, as a vegan Tunisian Jewish Djerban-inspired dish, typically appear as solid, individual baked goods with a moist and tender crumb texture rather than soupy or stew-like consistency. They have a rich brown color from chocolate with swirls or pockets of creamy, slightly lighter peanut butter mixed into the muffin batter. The peanut butter may appear as smooth streaks or small soft blobs of filling within the muffin structure.

They are usually served as individual
